void ctrmm ( char  side,
char  uplo,

complex *  b,
int  ldb 
)

ctrmm performs one of the triangular matrix-matrix multiplications for single precision complex numbers:

C := alpha * op( A) * B,

or

C := alpha * B * op( A)

alpha is a scalar. B is an m by n matrix, A is a unit, or non-unit, upper or lower triangular matrix.

Parameters:
[in]sidespecifies whether A appears on left or right.
side = 'L' or 'l', C := alpha * op( A) * B.
side = 'R' or 'r', C := alpha * B * op( A).
[in]uplospecifies whether upper or lower traingular part of A is referenced.
uplo = 'U' or 'u', upper traingular part of A is referenced.
uplo = 'L' or 'l', lower traingular part of A is referenced.
[in]transaspecifies the form of op( A ).
TRANSA = 'N' or 'n', op( A ) = A.
TRANSA = 'T' or 't', op( A ) = A'.
TRANSA = 'C' or 'C', op( A ) = A'.
[in]diagspecifies whether A is unit traingular or not.
diag = 'U' or 'u', A is unit triangular.
diag = 'N' or 'n', A is not unit triangular.
[in]mspecifies the number of rows of B.
[in]nspecifies the number of colums B.
[in]alphamultiplication factor on matrix product.
[in]apointer to matrix A.
[in]ldafirst dimension of A.
[in,out]bpointer to matrix B.
[in]ldbfirst dimension of B.
void ctrmmSC ( char  side,
char  uplo,
char  transa,
char  diag,

complex  alpha,
